cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.COM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes an analytical framework to investigate the integrated Sub-6GHz-mmWave cellular networks, which involves the study of network architecture, protocols, and algorithms. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper derives performance metrics such as signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio coverage probability and average achievable rate, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the deployment of mmWave small cells to provide high-quality service in traffic hotspots, which is related to multimedia applications. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the impact of various deployment parameters on the network performance, which is related to system design and control. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - Although less likely, the paper may also belong to this category as it discusses the deployment of cellular networks, which have a significant impact on society.
